Purple-leaf tea (Camellia sinensis L.) ameliorates high-fat diet induced obesity 
and metabolic disorder through the modulation of the gut microbiota in mice.

Lin YC(1), Lu HF(2)(3), Chen JC(4), Huang HC(5), Chen YH(6), Su YS(7), Tung 
CY(8)(9), Huang C(10)(11).

Author information:
(1)Department of Biotechnology and Laboratory Science in Medicine, National 
